   - Neutral, declarative, and observational.
   - No recommendations, guidance, or prescriptive language.
   - No causal verbs (e.g., “fixed”, “corrected”, “resolved by”, “addressed through”).

7. The narrative MUST explicitly communicate all of the following:
   - The applicable rule was evaluated in a subsequent governed audit run.
   - The violation condition was not observed in that run.
